    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "A. Community Development and Capacity Building\r\nidentification of livestock pockets by district Livestock Action Team by using poverty maps of the project districts; development of about 6,900 livestock groups with at least 35% women participation; social mobilization through local NGO's/CBO's ; community level extension by Community Livestock Assistants(CLS); capacity developement of farmer groups, DLS staff, partner NGO's/CBO's and livestock- based enterpreneurs.\r\nB. Livestock Productivity Improvement\r\nFifteen livestock improvement models identified as suitable for small and resource poor farmers; livestock productivity improvement through intensive forage development, provision of veterinary and breeding services(with emphasis on promotion of private practice), financing through microfinance intermediaries\r\nC. Livestock Processing and Marketing\r\nImprovement and/or establishment of milk market infrastructure (chilling centres) and retail outlets (dairy shops); meat processing marketing infrastructure development(slaughter houses/slabs/meat shops). improvement and/or establishment of live animal market/ market animal collection centres.\r\nD. Project Management Services\r\nA multi-sectoral project interventions for improved livelihood of the project beneficiaries.\r\nE. Higher Altitude Livelihood Pilot Project\r\nEstablishment of a central office led by a Project Manager, supported by technical assistance team to support project implementation."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
